Their [[Ujigami]] is {{Ill|Yamato Okunitama|lt=Yamato Okunitama|ja|倭大国魂神|simple}} of [[Ōyamato Shrine]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=International Symposium "Perspectives on Japanese history and literature from ancient historical records" |url=https://www.waseda.jp/inst/sgu/news-en/2019/04/12/5171 |access-date=2023-05-04 |website=Top Global University Project: Waseda Goes Global |language=en}}</ref>

{{ill|Yamato no Agoko|lt=Agoko no Sukune|ja|倭吾子籠}} was of the clan and governor of Yamato Province<ref>{{Cite web |title=Episode 61: Bad Behavior and the People that Excuse It |url=https://sengokudaimyo.com/podcast/episode-61 |access-date=2023-05-04 |website=Sengoku Daimyo |date=April 2022 |language=en-US}}</ref>

During [[Jimmu's Eastern Expedition]] {{ill|Shinetsuhiko|ja|椎根津彦}} was given the position by [[Emperor Jimmu]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Experts |first=Author : Japanese |title=Friday: Kojiki (「乞食」ではなく『古事記』ですヨ！！) #26 |url=https://japaneseexperts.net/972/ |access-date=2023-05-04 |website=Japanese Experts Net |language=en-US}}</ref> And Shinetsuhiko became their ancestor.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://d-museum.kokugakuin.ac.jp/eos/detail/id=9159 | title=Encyclopedia of Shinto詳細 }}</ref>

