* {{cite web |author=JHTI |year=2002 |title=Nihon Shoki |url=https://jhti.berkeley.edu/Nihon%20shoki.html |access-date=2019-08-23 |work=[[Japanese Historical Text Initiative]] (JHTI) |publisher=UC Berkeley}}, searchtext resource to retrieve kanbun text vs. English tr. (Aston) in blocs.
*{{cite book |last=Ujiya |first=Tsutomu (宇治谷孟) |title=Nihon shoki (日本書紀) |publisher=Kodansha |year=1988 |isbn=978-0-8021-5058-5 |volume=上}}, modern Japanese translation.
*{{cite book |last=Chamberlain |first=Basil Hall |title=The Kojiki |publisher=Kadokawa |year=1919 |oclc=1882339 |author-link=Basil Hall Chamberlain}} [http://www.sacred-texts.com/shi/kj/index.htm sacred texts]
